text: Kuzminovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Mrakovsky Selsoviet, Kugarchinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 83 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 5 km from Mrakovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kugarchinsky District
title: Kuzminovka, Kugarchinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
